Key Match Events: Moldova managed to break the deadlock, scoring a second goal thanks to a penalty just before the end of the first half.
Moldova took the lead as Mihail Caimacov’s direct freekick from the right gave goalkeeper Bonello no chance.
Four minutes in added time, Moldova doubled the score when they were awarded a penalty and from the penalty spot, Ion Nicolaescu converted.
Post-Match Reflections: Steve Borg and Enrico Pepe, Marcolini opted to start with Zach Muscat, Kurt Shaw and Jean Borg at the back.
On the other hand, Teddy Teuma still struggling to regain full fitness, Steve Pisani joined Matthew Guillaumier and Yannick Yankam in midfield.

Henry Bonello started in goal with Muscat, Shaw and Borg at the back, Joseph Mbong and Ryan Camenzuli on the flanks, Yankam, Guillaumier and Pisani in midfield with Paul Mbong and Kemar Reid employed up front.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The hosts went close after six minutes when Caimacov released Platica on the right and off the latter’s pass, Artur Ionita hit just wide.
Two minutes later, Ionita served Caimacov from the left and the latter controlled before hitting wide.
Ionita then had a powerful shot from outside the area which scraped past the post on 23 minutes.

Malta replied with a good cross by Ryan Camenzuli from the left and although Yannick Yankam failed to connect, Paul Mbong controlled the ball and tested goalkeeper Celeadnic with an angled shot from the right on 25 minutes.
Seven minutes later, Moldova took the lead as Mihail Caimacov’s direct freekick from the right gave goalkeeper Bonello no chance.
Four minutes in added time, Moldova doubled the score when they were awarded a penalty and from the penalty spot, Ion Nicolaescu converted.
